The alphabet is represented by 34 letters including <span style="font-size:175%">{{lang|ku-Arab|وو}}</span> which is given its own position. Kurds in [[Iraq]] and [[Iran]] mainly use this alphabet, though the Kurdish Latin alphabet is also in use. The standardization by KRG uses {{lang|ku-Arab|[[wikt:ک|ک]]}} (Unicode 06A9) instead of {{lang|ku-Arab|[[wikt:ك|ك]]}} (Unicode 0643) for letter Kaf (22 in above table), as listed in the Unicode table on the official home page for the standard.<ref name=":0" /> However, the latter glyph is still in use by various individuals and organizations.

