Similar to some English letters, both {{lang|ku-Arab|و}} (w) and {{lang|ku-Arab|ی}} (y) can become consonants. In the word {{lang|ku-Arab|وان}} (Wan) the {{lang|ku-Arab|و}} is consonant. Similarly, in the word {{lang|ku-Arab|یاری}} (play), the {{lang|ku-Arab|ی}} (y) is a consonant. Sorani stipulates that syllables must be formed with at least one vowel, whilst maximum two vowels are permitted.

==Historical alphabets==

===Cyrillic script===
A third system, used for the few (Kurmanji-speaking) Kurds in the former [[Soviet Union]], especially in Armenia, used a [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillic alphabet]], consisting of 40 letters.
It was designed in 1946 by [[Heciyê Cindî]]:<ref>{{cite book| author = Һ'. Щнди | chapter = | chapter-url = | format = | url =  | title = Әлифба | orig-year = | agency =  | edition = 3000 экз| location = Ереван| year = 1974 | publisher = Луйс| at = | volume = | issue = | pages = | page = 96 | series =  | isbn = | ref = }}</ref>
