'''Jeli Thuluth''' ({{lang-fa|جلي ثلث}}) is a [[calligraphic]] variety of [[Arabic language|Arabic]] script. This term was applied to writings in [[Thuluth]] script when the point of the pen employed was at least one centimeter broad. Jeli Thuluth was used in large panels and for inscriptions carved in stone on buildings or [[tombstone]]s.

